Comedy about Jack Pearson bringing his new wife to meet the family on Tyneside.
 



[b]Series 01[/b]
1/6 Jack takes his wife to meet the family, but they think she is just his new girlfriend.

2/6 Jack is hoping the good news about his book deal will help his mum to forgive him.

3/6 Sarah's parents visit Hebburn for the first time.

4/6 Dot buys Vicky a new car and nearly drives her off a mental cliff.

5/6 Joe is banned from his favourite foods and drinks just as Jack's stag night rolls around.

6/6 Jack and Sarah get ready for their wedding day. Of course, they are already married.
 
 
 




[b]Series 02[/b]
1/7 With a baby on the way, Sarah and Jack are desperate to move out of his parents' home.

2/7 Pauline is being bullied at work, but things are looking up for Jack and Sarah.

3/7 With Pauline away on a training weekend, Joe and Dot take advantage of being home alone.

4/7 Pauline's new cupcake business is thriving and Joe's recovery takes a romantic turn.

5/7 Jack's secret is out, as extracts of his pregnancy diary are published in a newspaper. ****

6/7 Sarah has more than her new baby to celebrate when she is offered a dream job overseas.

7/7 Ben, Susan and her monstrous mother Millie are stranded in Hebburn for Christmas.
